BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bbIg473rTcRPHcNm82PST
SUMMARY:LS 201: Small PA Mixing
DTSTAMP:20260403T051047Z
DTSTART:20260509T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Small PA Mixing workshop is designed to familiarize student
	s with running a small powered speaker system. Small PAs are generally use
	d for band practices\, acoustic sets\, DJ sets\, poetry readings\, protest
	s\, or even house shows and shows in Vera’s gallery space!. Topics will in
	clude: speaker amplification and setup\, practicing cable management and s
	ignal flow\, using EQ to ‘ring out’ a room\, and mixing for small room sho
	ws.\n\nYou must complete LS 101: Basics of Live Sound before you can take 
	this class.\n\nThis class is a prerequisite for the Front of House Mixing 
	class at Vera Project shows and access to VERA’s PA rental system. Each Li
	ve Sound class unlocks new audio engineering volunteer shifts at Vera and 
	eventually paid opportunities in and outside of the venue. Become a volunt
	eer at Vera to access other audio-related educational programs such as tou
	rs\, field trips\, and internships.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/Od8d5bbd302e\n
	\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/Od8d5bbd302e
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
